Reasoning: The paper discusses the challenges of designing dependable computer networks and the advent of Software-Defined Networks (SDNs) to provide flexibility in updating networks. This topic falls under the category of computer networks and distributed computing, which is covered by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses algorithmic techniques and optimization problems, which are covered by cs.AL (Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the consistency properties of network updates, which falls under the category of control and systems engineering, covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control).
